# Styling

## Article Body

Article content uses the `.article-body` class (not Tailwind prose). Styles are in `globals.css` and cover:
- Headings (h2/h3/h4 with explicit sizes, white color, bold)
- Paragraphs (1.8 line-height, 1.25em vertical margins)
- Lists (`list-style: disc inside` for ul, `decimal inside` for ol)
- Code blocks (highlight.js Atom One Dark theme)
- Links (orange with transparent underline that fades in on hover, using `:any-link` for specificity over Tailwind reset)
- Blockquotes (orange left border, italic, muted color)
- Images (lazy, rounded, vertical margins)

Tailwind's reset strips list markers and link colors. Always use high-specificity selectors (`.article-body ul`, `.article-body a:any-link`) to override.

## Theme Colors (CSS Variables)

```
--color-primary: #ff5420 (orange)
--color-secondary: #ff1343 (red)
--color-bg: #222
--color-surface: #2a2a2a
--color-text: #fff
--color-text-muted: #8d9297
--color-border: #3a3a3a
```

## Gradient Text

Use the `.text-gradient` class for orange-to-red gradient text. Does NOT work inside `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` — use explicit white color for article headings instead.
